MLEN.column_description: List of failed filters (if any) or "PASS" indicating the variant has passed all filters.

CIPOS.column_description: Allele frequency in the EUR populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

end_position.column_description: End position (0-based). Corresponds to the first base after the last base in the reference allele.

start_position.column_description: Start position (0-based). Corresponds to the first base of the string of reference bases.

no_call.column_description: Total read depth; only low coverage data were counted towards the DP, exome data were not used

MSTART.column_description: Confidence interval around END for imprecise variants

DP.column_description: Mitochondrial end coordinate of inserted sequence

quality.column_description: Total number of alternate alleles in called genotypes

CS.column_description: Allele frequency in the AFR populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

filter.column_description: Estimated allele frequency in the range (0,1)

hom_ref_call.column_description: Total number of alleles in called genotypes

IMPRECISE.column_description: Allele frequency in the AMR populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

VT.column_description: Mitochondrial start coordinate of inserted sequence

MEND.column_description: Phred-scaled quality score (-10log10 prob(call is wrong)). Higher values imply better quality.

alternate_bases.column_description: One record for each alternate base (if any).

OLD_VARIANT.column_description: Precise Target Site Duplication for bases, if unknown, value will be NULL

AN.column_description: Mobile element info of the form NAME,START,END<POLARITY; If there is only 5' OR 3' support for this call, will be NULL NULL for START and END

EX_TARGET.column_description: SV length. It is only calculated for structural variation MEIs. For other types of SVs; one may calculate the SV length by INFO:END-START+1, or by finding the difference between lengthes of REF and ALT alleles

call.column_description: Ancestral Allele. Format: AA|REF|ALT|IndelType. AA: Ancestral allele, REF:Reference Allele, ALT:Alternate Allele, IndelType:Type of Indel (REF, ALT and IndelType are only defined for indels)

MC.column_description: Allele frequency in the SAS populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

CIEND.column_description: Allele frequency in the EAS populations calculated from AC and AN, in the range (0,1)

SVLEN.column_description: Confidence interval around POS for imprecise variants
